# Environment Configuration Template

## Create .env file in frontend directory

```bash
# API Configuration
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# For Production (Vercel)
# REACT_APP_API_URL=https://your-backend-api.com/api

# Other configurations (if needed)
# REACT_APP_STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=your_stripe_key
# REACT_APP_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=your_maps_key
```

## Vercel Environment Variables Setup

1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
2. Navigate to: **Settings → Environment Variables**
3. Add the following variables:

| Variable Name | Value | Environment |
|--------------|-------|-------------|
| `REACT_APP_API_URL` | `https://your-backend-url.com/api` | Production |
| `REACT_APP_API_URL` | `http://localhost:5000/api` | Development |

## Important Notes

- All React environment variables MUST start with `REACT_APP_`
- After adding/changing environment variables in Vercel, you must redeploy
- Environment variables are embedded at build time, not runtime
- Never commit `.env` file to Git (it's in .gitignore)

## Testing Environment Variables

Add this to any component to test:
```javascript
console.log('API URL:', process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL);
```

## Redeploy After Changes

```bash
vercel --prod
```
